{"section": "Exercise 3.11.2: Proving explicit formulas for recurrence relations by induction.", "qid": 1, "instructions": "<div class=\"setup\">\n <p>\n  Prove each of the following statements using mathematical induction.\n </p>\n</div>\n", "input_type": null, "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <span class=\"part\">\n  (b)\n </span>\n <div class=\"text\">\n  <p>\n   Define the sequence {b\n   <sub>\n    n\n   </sub>\n   } as follows:\n  </p>\n  <ul>\n   <li>\n    <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n     b\n     <sub>\n      0\n     </sub>\n     = 1\n    </span>\n   </li>\n   <li>\n    <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n     b\n     <sub>\n      k\n     </sub>\n     = 2b\n     <sub>\n      k-1\n     </sub>\n     + 1\n    </span>\n    for\n    <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n     k \u2265 1\n    </span>\n   </li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>\n   Prove that for\n   <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n    n \u2265 0\n   </span>\n   ,\n   <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n    b\n    <sub>\n     n\n    </sub>\n    = 2\n    <sup>\n     n+1\n    </sup>\n    - 1\n   </span>\n   .\n  </p>\n </div>\n</div>\n", "choices": [], "correct_choice_index": null, "answer": "", "explanation": null}